> The Fizz Buzz problem is a classic coding challenge that requires you to write a program that prints out all numbers from 1 to 100, but for multiples of three print "Fizz" instead, and for multiples of five print "Buzz". Here is the JavaScript code that solves the Fizz Buzz problem:

```javascript
for (var i = 1; i <= 100; i++) {
  if (i % 3 === 0 && i % 5 === 0) {
    console.log("Fizz Buzz");
  } else if (i % 3 === 0) {
    console.log("Fizz");
  } else if (i % 5 === 0) {
    console.log("Buzz");
  } else {
    console.log(i);
  }
}
```

> This code uses a for loop to iterate from 1 to 100, and for each number it checks if it is divisible by 3 or 5 using the % operator. If the number is divisible by both 3 and 5, it prints "Fizz Buzz". If it is only divisible by 3, it prints "Fizz". If it is only divisible by 5, it prints "Buzz". Otherwise, it prints the number itself.","textTemplate":"","startCharIdx":2,"endCharIdx":920,"metadataSeparator":"
