{"id_":"308dc49b-a5ba-4a83-8908-cc2d3fb82d87","metadata":{"file_path":"/workspaces/andrewford-co-nz-chatbot/data/chatgpt-macos-ios-using-shortcuts.md","file_name":"chatgpt-macos-ios-using-shortcuts.md","private":"false"},"excludedEmbedMetadataKeys":[],"excludedLlmMetadataKeys":[],"relationships":{"SOURCE":{"nodeId":"./data/chatgpt-macos-ios-using-shortcuts.md_5","metadata":{"file_path":"/workspaces/andrewford-co-nz-chatbot/data/chatgpt-macos-ios-using-shortcuts.md","file_name":"chatgpt-macos-ios-using-shortcuts.md","private":"false"},"hash":"D3Vp7Tb5rkd+Kkuo0gLG8arRx1iW0RcIi/sGngIJw0M="}},"text":"## Creating a "shortcut" using the ChatGPT API

**🚨 Update 🚨**

**Since I wrote this Open AI have released an iOS app with a shortcut action see how it works here.**

{% image "./openai-create-new-key.png", "How to create an OpenAI key" %}

To be able to use the Shortcut I've created you will need to first create an account with OpenAI. Head to their sign up page, fill in your details then got to the View API Keys page. Follow the instructions above.

{% image "./openai-api-key-generated.png", "Generate OpenAI key" %}

You then need to create an API key to use with our Shortcut, click on the "+ Create new secret key" button. Copy the new key by clicking the green button.

Either on macOS or on iOS click this link to my shortcut and "Add Shortcut".

Open up the shortcut (right click and Edit on macOS) to edit. Paste the key into the Text section of the shortcut shown in the image below and close the shortcut.

{% image "./add-key-shortcut.png", "Add key to shortcut" %}

For personal use they credited $18 until May for me when I created an account. I've barely run up any credit so far. Under $0.10, in fact it's very cheap.","textTemplate":"","startCharIdx":2,"endCharIdx":1142,"metadataSeparator":"
","type":"TEXT","hash":"cI9kIxa7TWQ86lYAEct6sTcxwe33rjMOp0srAsmfhhA="}

