{"id_":"f6fe8707-ba7e-4faf-95ba-45fac717b258","metadata":{"file_path":"/workspaces/andrewford-co-nz-chatbot/data/shop-nextjs-stripe-introduction.md","file_name":"shop-nextjs-stripe-introduction.md","private":"false"},"excludedEmbedMetadataKeys":[],"excludedLlmMetadataKeys":[],"relationships":{"SOURCE":{"nodeId":"./data/shop-nextjs-stripe-introduction.md_1","metadata":{"file_path":"/workspaces/andrewford-co-nz-chatbot/data/shop-nextjs-stripe-introduction.md","file_name":"shop-nextjs-stripe-introduction.md","private":"false"},"hash":"uahXRWF88Vuojpne7BZcIS6NC3OCPggVmZCcn72+ur0="},"PREVIOUS":{"nodeId":"7472b1cb-4edc-447f-9165-6788a3afc06a","metadata":{"file_path":"/workspaces/andrewford-co-nz-chatbot/data/shop-nextjs-stripe-introduction.md","file_name":"shop-nextjs-stripe-introduction.md","private":"false"},"hash":"NMA081+hn84rJFwzFJYrh8Iuk5oEiOVM/RshRLsDFpU="},"NEXT":{"nodeId":"07034afa-7b7e-42eb-8f7d-075c6e5d93d1","metadata":{},"hash":"qAabl0C5vqbGjM8JZNE4xomNntvwq7h+jPilQqXheek="}},"text":"You will see 3 folders.The "pages" folder is where the routing happens.That will direct the url page in your app.For example if you had a file called `contact-us.js` to be routed to it you would have the following url your browser `http://localhost:3000/contact-us`. This will show the content from that component.Your **pages** folder will have a **api** folder and two files `_app.js` and `index.js`.Open the project in a browser and you should see something like this

{% image "./nextjs-start.png", "Next.JS Starter" %}

Great the project is up and running in development mode 🙌

In your code editor (I suggest you use VS Code) we will open the `index.js` file in the `pages` folder.We are going to remove everything and replace it with the following:

```jsx
import Head from "next/head";

export default function Home() {
  return (
    <>
      <Head>
        <title>Products</title>
        <meta name="description" content="Products" />
      </Head>
    </>
  );
}
```

That's cleared the standard install documentation links.Time to make our first component.Let's make a new folder called `components` and add a file `layout.js` in that directory.Add the following:

```jsx
import React from "react";
import Head from "next/head";

import styles from "../styles/layout.module.css";

export const Layout = ({ children }) => {
  return (
    <>
      <Head>
        <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
      </Head>
      <div className={styles.container}>
        <main className={styles.main}>{children}</main>
      </div>
    </>
  );
};
```

This will be the layout shared across all our pages in the shop.To add to that we will add a Header and a Footer component.Again in the `components` folder create a `header.js` and a `footer.js` file.","textTemplate":"","metadataSeparator":"
